description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you regularly see things that can be improved?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Projects and Service Change Facilitator role provides an ideal opportunity to work with clinical, non-clinical and corporate teams to help review, re-design and deliver transformational change in the way we provide care to our patients and improve the working lives of our staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our aim is to &lt;em&gt;‘create a way of working which engages staff in continuously improving and sustaining the delivery of safe, high quality, efficient and financially sustainable services to patients’.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone who has experience of service redesign and change management of health and care services, who can facilitate collaborative working and has excellent communication skills. You will need to have a positive and engaging approach, be able to bring people with you and ensure that the process of change is well managed and results sustained. Knowledge of the theory and practice of change management and service development tools and techniques is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can provide you with the opportunity to be part of an enthusiastic and experienced team of project and service development professionals who are dedicated to making changes which make a difference to our patients and staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in discussing this post please email Chris Davis, christine.davis8@nhs.net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our vision is to provide safe, high quality seamless services delivered with courtesy and respect. To achieve our vision we expect all our staff to uphold our Trust values. Our Trust values are: &lt;br /&gt; Honesty, Openness &amp; Integrity&lt;br /&gt; Fairness&lt;br /&gt; Inclusion &amp; Collaboration&lt;br /&gt; Respect &amp; Dignity&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;***Preference will be given to staff with ‘Priority’ and &#39;At Risk&#39; status including NHS At Risk staff throughout Devon.***&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;DUE TO THE ANTICIPATED HIGH NUMBER OF APPLICATIONS FOR THIS POST WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE THE VACANCY BEFORE THE CLOSING DATE.&lt;/p&gt;
